Leave a 'YES' if you've ever felt exactly like this when you've jumped to a conclusion 😂👇Our minds are so quick to make assumptions and judgements. Whether its on other people, or a situation that happened, or how someone has reacted toward us. Most of the time, our minds jump to assuming the worst. And then most of the time, we discover it wasn't what we thought at all. And that anxiety, stress, and anger we chalked up in our heads was for nothing. Remember when you're starting to assume, to take a deep breath, and be patient to understand a situation fully.
